            <div class="carousel-caption">
                <h1>Text headline 3...</h1>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Controls -->
    <a class="left carousel-control" href="#myCarousel" data-slide="prev">
        <span class="icon-prev"></span>
    </a>
    <a class="right carousel-control" href="#myCarousel" data-slide="next">
        <span class="icon-next"></span>
    </a>
</div>

<div class="section">

    <div class="container">

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4">
                <h3>Who Are We?</h3>
                <p>The world is changing, but not often in the ways we want it and not always for its people. We do millions of things that change our environment. We are happy when they succeed. Many of us do a lot of things that could have a multiplying and positive impact if only they were shared and known. They also fail but this does not mean that, if tried again or in other settings with a few modifications or adaptations, they will not succeed. @Html.ActionLink("Read More>>>", "WhoAreWe", "AboutUs")</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4">
                <h3>History</h3>
                <p>IDoThisforChange Inc., was founded in 2016 as an independent, not-for-profit organization. It is essentially a citizen public forum that gathers small and big initiatives that have worked and brought about positive changes in families, workplaces, communities, nations and the world. Participants describe in writing, video or audio files what they do or have done that brought about positive change(s). It is an practical exchange platform for all —scientists, educators, or people from any walk of life— to share, read and listen to what others are doing for a better world. @Html.ActionLink("Read More>>>", "History", "AboutUs")</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4">
                <h3>Become a Sponsor</h3>
                <p>ThisIdoforchange is an independent public platform that has no affiliation to any corporation, public or private. @Html.ActionLink("Read More>>>", "BecomeSponsor", "Donate")</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <!-- /.row -->

    </div>
    <!-- /.container -->

</div>
